  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Off-Grid Electrification for Rural Communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A USTDA grant to Havenhill Synergy Limited funds a feasibility study to support the development and deployment of up to 110 solar with battery storage minigrid systems to be deployed in rural communities in Nigeria. The project will deliver new reliable electricity and will support the goals of Nigeria&apos;s Rural Electrification Agency in enhancing electricity access in unserved and underserved communities. The feasibility study will be undertaken on a sole source basis by the U.S. firm Odyssey Energy Solutions, Inc.. A USTDA grant to Havenhill Synergy Limited funds a feasibility study to support the development and deployment of up to 110 solar with battery storage minigrid systems to be deployed in rural communities in Nigeria. The project will deliver new reliable electricity and will support the goals of Nigeria&apos;s Rural Electrification Agency in enhancing electricity access in unserved and underserved communities.</narrative>
  </description>
